This repository's canonical agent manual is AGENTS.md at the repo root —
read it before any work, follow its operating model (ground → plan →
implement → verify → encode feedback) and its hard rules:

- Layering app → features → shared is lint-enforced; features expose only
  index.ts; never import @react-navigation/* (expo-router forked it).
- Zod-validate every edge; Zustand stores with selectors; process.env only in
  src/shared/lib/env.ts.
- NativeWind className only (cn() for conditionals); shared/ui primitives;
  testID on every interactive element; tests in __tests__/, never src/app/.
- Conventional Commits; npm run verify must pass; update stale docs in the
  same change; docs map lives in AGENTS.md.

When a rule here disagrees with AGENTS.md, AGENTS.md wins.
